{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774367529,"nonce":"HaWfAeuJbdXaj2ENhBkufc7h1as=","message":"## Run 4: All Phase 2 results complete (TPU v4-8)\n\n### Final results table — ALL conditions\n\n| Condition | nn_output | Loss change | Ep error | Peak speed | SISU 0→1 velocity |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **running_cost** | 1e-5 | 32→3 (-91%) | 0.007 | 3.33 | **-0.3%** |\n| **CVaR 10%** | 1e-5 | 32→17 (-49%) | 0.109 | 3.18 | **-0.9%** |\n| **nn_1e-6** (low cost) | 1e-6 | 32→5 (-83%) | 0.070 | 3.91 | **-0.7%** |\n| **nn_1e-4** (high cost) | 1e-4 | 32→714 (DIVERGED) | 0.780 | 2.63 | +4.1% (invalid) |\n| combined | 1e-5 | 11→5 (-54%) | 0.152 | 2.06 | N/A |\n| softmin | 1e-5 | DIVERGED | - | - | - |\n| default | 1e-5 | DIVERGED | - | - | - |\n\n### Key findings\n\n1. **No SISU-dependent peak velocity in any converged condition.** All converged models show -0.3% to -0.9% change (noise-level decrease, not the predicted increase).\n\n2. **Control cost affects absolute speed** (3.91 at 1e-6 vs 3.33 at 1e-5 vs diverged at 1e-4) but NOT SISU-dependent modulation.\n\n3. **CVaR worsens convergence** without producing the target signature. Training is harder (loss only drops to 17 vs 3) and accuracy is worse (0.109 vs 0.007).\n\n4. **Decoupled SISU test reveals accuracy modulation**: at fixed perturbation, varying SISU improves endpoint accuracy by ~11% at mid-SISU values. The network IS using SISU for gain modulation, just not for velocity.\n\n### Interpretation\n\nThe LQG separation principle is confirmed experimentally: expected-cost optimization (including CVaR approximation) changes feedback gains but not trajectory shape. The velocity signature requires genuine minimax (H-infinity) optimization — adversarial perturbation training (APT) or a fundamentally different loss structure.\n\n### Figures\n4 HTML figures at results/part2_5/figures/:\n- fig_peak_velocity_by_sisu.html\n- fig_endpoint_error_by_sisu.html\n- fig_lateral_deviation_by_sisu.html\n- fig_loss_curves.html\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}